<h2>Wales-Specific Requirements</h2>

<div style="background: #fff3cd; border-left: 4px solid #ffc107; padding: 15px; margin: 15px 0;">
  <strong>Rent Smart Wales</strong><br>
  If you are a landlord in Wales, you must be registered with Rent Smart Wales. While Rent Smart Wales registration
  is primarily relevant to possession proceedings, courts may consider your registration status as evidence of
  compliance with Welsh landlord obligations.
</div>

<h2>Important: Follow Pre-Action Protocol First</h2>

<p><strong>⚠️ DO NOT file the N1 claim immediately.</strong> You MUST first:</p>
<ol>
  <li>Send the <strong>Letter Before Claim</strong> to the defendant by first class post or email</li>
  <li>Enclose the <strong>Information Sheet</strong>, <strong>Reply Form</strong>, and <strong>Financial Statement Form</strong></li>
  <li>Wait <strong>30 days</strong> for the defendant to respond or pay</li>
  <li>Keep proof of sending (certificate of posting or email confirmation)</li>
</ol>

<p>
If you do not follow the Pre-Action Protocol for Debt Claims, the court may:
</p>
<ul>
  <li>Strike out your claim</li>
  <li>Order you to pay the defendant's costs</li>
  <li>Refuse to award you interest or legal costs</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Only proceed to court if:</strong></p>
<ul>
  <li>The defendant does not respond within 30 days, OR</li>
  <li>The defendant refuses to pay or disputes the debt without valid reason, OR</li>
  <li>You cannot agree a reasonable payment plan</li>
</ul>

<h2>Filing steps (after 30-day pre-action period)</h2>
<ol>
  <li>File online via Money Claim Online (MCOL) at www.moneyclaim.gov.uk (recommended — faster and cheaper), OR</li>
  <li>Print the N1 PDF on white A4 and send by post to County Court Money Claims Centre</li>
  <li>Attach the particulars, arrears schedule, interest sheet and evidence index</li>
  <li>Include proof that you sent the Letter Before Claim and waited 30 days</li>
  <li>Pay the court fee (see Filing Guide for fee table)</li>
</ol>

